	title = {The {Star} {Formation} {Rate} bi-modality in galaxies at low redshift},
	abstract = {My colleagues and I have investigated the presence of two different populations of galaxies in the star formation rate-stellar mass plane using the Sloan Digital Sky Survey data at redshift 𝑧 ∼ 0. After having worked with different catalogues, we have inferred that the presence of a main star-forming sequence and of a passive one could be explained by considering galaxies as open systems with different feedback processes which slow down the star formation at high stellar masses, for instance the presence of Active Galactic Nuclei. In this framework the star formation rate depends mainly on the inflow of gas from the outer environment, and this process overall stops when a maximum dark matter halo mass of 𝑀ℎ𝑎𝑙𝑜 ∼ 1012 − 1013 𝑀⊙ is reached. This mechanism is able to explain the generally higher masses of passive galaxies with respect to the ones on the main sequence.},
